To mark specific days in a Calendar control in a C# project, you can use the `AddBoldedDate()` method to mark the desired dates in a bold font style. Here is an example:

```csharp
DateTime[] importantDates = new DateTime[]
{
    new DateTime(2022, 1, 12),
    new DateTime(2022, 1, 21),
    new DateTime(2022, 2, 5),
};

foreach (DateTime date in importantDates)
{
    calendarControl.AddBoldedDate(date);
}

calendarControl.UpdateBoldedDates();
```

In this example, an array `importantDates` is created to hold the dates that need to be marked. You can customize the array according to your desired dates.

The `AddBoldedDate()` method is then used to add each date from the `importantDates` array to the Calendar control. Finally, the `UpdateBoldedDates()` method is called to update the Calendar control and display the marked dates in a bold font style.

Make sure that you have a Calendar control named `calendarControl` or replace it with the actual name of your Calendar control in the code.

By running this code, the specified dates will be marked in the Calendar control.

