```csharp
protected void calendarControl_DayRender(object sender, DayRenderEventArgs e)
{
    e.Cell.Attributes["onclick"] = "return false";
}
```

In this example, the `DayRender` event is handled and the `onclick` attribute of each cell is set to `"return false"`. This prevents the postback event from occurring when the user clicks on any date, effectively disabling the click.

Make sure to subscribe to the `DayRender` event of the Calendar control either in the designer or programmatically using `calendarControl.DayRender += calendarControl_DayRender;`.

By using this approach, all dates in the Calendar control will no longer be clickable, effectively preventing user interaction with the calendar.

